  "decision_conditions": [
    "Freeholder",
    "The development must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date hereof.\r\rReason: To comply with Section 18 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990, as amended.",
    "Prior to commencement of the development, a Method Statement, detailing the method of construction/repair for the works hereby permitted, shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.\r\rReason: To enable the Local Planning Authority to control the works in detail to protect the character and appearance of the listed building and to not result in harm to the heritage asset in accordance with Policies 28 and 30 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018.",
    "All external facing materials, treatments and finishes shall be similar to those of the original wall and maintained and retained thereafter. Where this is not possible the type and treatment of the materials to be used shall be agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the development being carried out. \r\rReason: To ensure that the proposed development would not result in harm to the visual amenities of the area and the heritage asset in accordance with Policies 28 and 30 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018.",
    "Any damage caused to the building by the carrying out of the works hereby approved shall be reported immediately to the Local Planning Authority and details of such remedial works as may be deemed necessary shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the works carried out in accordance with the approved details within 2 months and thereafter so retained. \r\rReason: To ensure that the internal character, appearance and fabric of the building is safeguarded and to accord with the requirements of Policy 30 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018."
  ],
